headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 28 points, Bobby Portis scored 17 of his 19 points in the first half and the Milwaukee Bucks defeated the Orlando Magic 127-110 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks win 4th straight behind 28 from Antetokounmpo

headlines.description: — Miami had eight players available, losing one after he had completed his pregame warmup. Washington had players getting crash courses in Wizards terminology a couple hours before actually getting into the game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Depleted Heat hold off depleted Wizards, 119-112

headlines.description: — Tobias Harris had 19 points, 12 rebounds, and 10 assists for his first career triple-double, Joel Embiid finished with 36 points and 11 rebounds, and the Philadelphia 76ers hung on to beat the Toronto Raptors 114-109 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris has first career triple-double as Sixers beat Raptors

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — LeBron James and Russell Westbrook both had triple-doubles and the Los Angeles Lakers snapped a season-high, five-game skid with a 132-123 victory over the Houston Rockets on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: James, Westbrook have triple-doubles, Lakers' skid ends at 5

events.name: New York Knicks at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Mitchell Robinson had 14 points and a season-high 18 rebounds, Julius Randle added 13 points and 15 boards, and the New York Knicks topped the short-handed Minnesota Timberwolves 96-88 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks overcome cold shooting to beat Wolves, 96-88

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Garrett Temple nailed four of his five fourth-quarter 3-pointers in a decisive flurry and rookie Herb Jones scored a career-high 26 points to lift the New Orleans Pelicans to a near-record 108-104 comeback victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Temple, Jones rally Pelicans past Cavaliers after Rubio hurt

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry became the first player in NBA history to make 3,000 career 3-pointers on Tuesday night in a game where the Denver Nuggets barely held off the NBA-leading Golden State Warriors 89-86.

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton had 24 points and 10 assists, and the Sacramento Kings held off the Oklahoma City Thunder 117-111 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton helps Kings topple short-handed Thunder 117-111
